text: Narbutovo () is a rural locality (a village) in Yumaguzinsky Selsoviet, Kugarchinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 24 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 36 km from Mrakovo, 6 km from Yumaguzino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kugarchinsky District
title: Narbutovo
